        "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nOn the JSON Schema blog page, the logo on the left side of the header slightly overflows its container, causing a visual misalignment in the top navigation bar.\n\n<img width=\"1512\" height=\"982\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/88deea19-e701-4716-ba02-50a89d47e401\" />\n\n### Steps To Reproduce\n\n1.\tOpen https://json-schema.org/blog\n2.\tObserve the top-left header area\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nThe logo should stay properly contained within the header and align cleanly with the navigation items.\n\n\n### Screenshots\n\n_No response_\n\n### Device Information [optional]\n\n```markdown\n- OS:\n- Browser:\n- version:\n```\n\n### Are you working on this issue?\n\nYes\n\n### Do you think this work might require an [Architectural Decision Record (ADR)]? (significant or noteworthy)\n\nNo",
