        "body": "### What Docs changes are you proposing?\n\nDescription\n\n    While running the JSON Schema website locally, I noticed that Draft 2019-09 already uses the same layout components as newer drafts (e.g. 2020-12), but feels less consistent and harder to read due to presentation differences rather than navigation or functionality.\n  \n  I’d like to propose small, presentation-only improvements to improve readability and visual consistency, without changing navigation, sidebar grouping, or specification content.\n\nProposed scope\n\t•\tImprove typography and spacing (headings, paragraphs, lists)\n\t•\tImprove Markdown rendering readability using existing styles/components\n\nOut of scope:\n  No navigation changes, no spec text changes, no reclassification of the draft.\n\nIf this approach is acceptable, pls assign me on this PR, I'll be happy to work on it.\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
